The paper focuses on video saliency detection using deep learning models, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model also incorporates memory and attention mechanisms, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of motion information in the model suggests that it may also fall under multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves training and optimization of the model, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks in the proposed model suggests that it may also fall under neural networks (cs.NE).
